#compdef dockrtui
# =============================================================================
# dockrtui — Julien Denizot's "A fast, modern and
#          keyboard-driven terminal dashboard for Docker
#          — built with Rust and ratatui" — a TUI
#          alternative to the official Docker Desktop
#          GUI + lazydocker that provides at-a-glance
#          dashboards of running containers, available
#          images, declared networks, mounted volumes,
#          and detected docker-compose projects, with
#          vim-style keyboard navigation + quick
#          actions (start / stop / restart / inspect /
#          prune / exec-shell) without leaving the
#          terminal.
#          Distinguishing from lazydocker (Jesse Duffield's
#          Go-implemented Docker TUI; the established
#          choice in this niche; uses Docker Engine API
#          via fsouza/go-dockerclient), Portainer (web-
#          based Docker GUI; heavier deploy footprint),
#          official Docker Desktop (Electron-based GUI;
#          macOS/Windows-only commercial under the
#          Docker subscription model), ctop (Bryan
#          Schwartz's older top-like container CLI;
#          read-only, no actions), and docui (Yusuke
#          Sato's older Docker TUI) by:
#            - BOLLARD FOUNDATION — uses fussybeaver/
#              bollard v0.19.4 with the `ssl` feature
#              (this is the headline CLI library that
#              OPENS Axis 44 on the Rust side; see
#              taxonomy notes below) for all Docker
#              Engine API operations: container CRUD,
#              image pull/push/build, network create/
#              connect, volume manage/prune.  Pure-Rust
#              async Docker client; no shell-out to the
#              `docker` binary needed for any
#              dashboard operation
#            - RATATUI 0.29 TUI — built on the Axis 28
#              ratatui + crossterm 0.29 stack with
#              modern Rust 2024 edition; responsive
#              layout with minimum terminal size 70×28
#              enforced at startup with a friendly
#              error message
#            - DUAL ASYNC RUNTIMES — uses BOTH tokio
#              (full features) AND smol concurrently;
#              tokio handles long-running Docker API
#              calls (streaming logs, exec sessions);
#              smol handles smaller event-driven UI
#              tasks; async-channel + futures-lite
#              bridge between the two runtimes
#            - ANIMATED SPLASH SCREEN — on startup,
#              dockrtui displays a percentage-progress
#              splash screen as it connects to the
#              Docker socket + queries initial inventory
#              (containers/images/networks/volumes/
#              compose projects); SplashEvent
#              messages flow from the connection task
#              into the splash screen via channels
#            - SOCKET AUTO-DETECTION — checks (in
#              priority order):
#              1. DOCKER_HOST env-var (same as Docker
#                 CLI)
#              2. Rootless Docker: /run/user/$UID/
#                 docker.sock
#              3. Classic rootful: /var/run/docker.sock
#              Works out-of-the-box with Docker Desktop,
#              Docker rootless, and classic Docker
#              Engine installations
#            - QUICK ACTIONS — single-key actions for
#              containers (start [s] / stop [S] /
#              restart [r] / kill [k] / pause/resume),
#              images (pull [P] / remove [d] / prune
#              [x]), networks (create / inspect / rm),
#              volumes (list / inspect / delete /
#              prune)
#            - SMART SEARCH + FILTERING — `/` opens a
#              search prompt; results filter live as
#              the user types; supports filtering by
#              container name, image tag, network
#              name, volume name, or compose project
#            - BUILT-IN SHELL inside CONTAINERS —
#              vim-style binding (typically `e`)
#              opens an interactive shell inside the
#              selected container via Docker Exec API
#              (`docker exec -it <id> sh`); supports
#              cd, command history, autocomplete
#              within the embedded shell
#            - COMPOSE INTEGRATION — detects local
#              `docker-compose.yml` / `compose.yaml`
#              files; treats them as grouped objects;
#              allows up/down/restart/build operations
#              against the entire project (not just
#              individual containers)
#            - VOLUME MANAGEMENT — list/inspect/
#              delete/prune unused volumes from
#              within the TUI; uses bollard's volumes
#              API
#            - COLOR-EYRE ERROR HANDLING — uses
#              color-eyre v0.6 (Jane Lusby's
#              `color_eyre` crate; the canonical
#              Rust panic-aware error reporter with
#              pretty terminal formatting); errors
#              propagate to the terminal with
#              syntax-highlighted stack traces
#            - PANIC HOOK + ALTERNATE SCREEN — on
#              panic, dockrtui restores the terminal
#              from alternate-screen mode + cleans
#              up cursor + disables raw mode before
#              the panic message propagates; users
#              don't end up with a broken terminal
#              after a crash
#            - CARGO INSTALL — `cargo install
#              dockrtui` is the canonical install
#              path; pre-built binaries also
#              available via GitHub Releases for
#              Linux + WSL2 (the project's tested
#              platforms)
#            - 125+ STARS ON LuuNa-JD/dockrtui —
#              modest but growing; active maintenance
#              by Julien Denizot (Orbitnet, France;
#              software + cloud developer specialized
#              in digital health systems)
#          Used by: Docker users tired of shell-out-
#          to-docker workflows for daily container
#          monitoring + management, lazydocker users
#          curious about a Rust+ratatui alternative,
#          DevOps engineers preferring terminal-based
#          dashboards for SSH'd remote-host management,
#          and developers running docker-compose-based
#          local stacks who want a single-pane view
#          across their project's services.
#
# Author:  Julien Denizot (LuuNa-JD on GitHub;
#          denizot.j@orbitnet.fr); software + cloud
#          developer at Orbitnet, France, specialized
#          in digital-health-system engineering.
#          Portfolio at https://luuna-jd.github.io/
#          portfolio/.
# Source:  https://github.com/LuuNa-JD/dockrtui
#          https://github.com/LuuNa-JD/dockrtui/blob/main/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/LuuNa-JD/dockrtui/blob/main/src/app.rs
#          https://github.com/LuuNa-JD/dockrtui/blob/main/Cargo.toml
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; dockrtui is a TUI
#          application with NO command-line flags
#          beyond the standard `--help` / `--version`
#          provided implicitly.  Once launched, all
#          interaction is keyboard-driven inside the
#          ratatui interface.
# Library: bollard v0.19.4 with the `ssl` feature
#          (fussybeaver/bollard — "An asynchronous
#          Docker daemon API").  This is the headline
#          dependency for this completion's axis-44
#          opening role; see taxonomy notes below.
#          Also ratatui v0.29 + crossterm v0.29 (Axis
#          28 TUI), tokio v1 with `full` + smol v2 +
#          async-channel v2.5 + futures-lite v2.6 +
#          futures-util v0.3 (dual async runtime
#          architecture), color-eyre v0.6 (Axis 6
#          panic-aware error reporter), anyhow v1
#          (Axis 6 errors), serde_json v1, chrono v0.4
#          (date/time formatting for "container started
#          X ago"), uuid v1 with `v4` (session IDs),
#          rand v0.9 (splash animation jitter).
# License: MIT
# Status:  125+ stars on LuuNa-JD/dockrtui; active
#          development (latest commit 2026-04-24);
#          version 0.1.3; published to crates.io as
#          `dockrtui`.  Rust 2024 edition required.
#          Tested on Linux + WSL2.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY — AXIS 44 OPENS:
#   DOCKER CLIENT / CONTAINER ORCHESTRATION
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This completion **OPENS AXIS 44** in the cross-
# language CLI library taxonomy: Docker Client /
# Container Orchestration (libraries that wrap the
# Docker Engine API + Docker Socket protocol to
# enable CLI tools to manage containers/images/
# networks/volumes/compose projects without shelling
# out to the `docker` binary — as distinct from
# Axis 43 Git Library which wraps git operations,
# or Axis 26 Web Frameworks which serve HTTP).
#
# Pattern: R764 123rd language (Ante) closes the
# prior 3+1 cycle → R765 Rust=99 (dockrtui/bollard
# → Axis 44 OPENS THIS) is the first leader bump
# in the new cycle; the next Rust bump (R769) will
# hit the **100-library-per-language landmark** on
# the Rust side, mirroring the 100-library milestones
# previously crossed by Go (R731) and TS-Node
# (R??).  Pending: R766 Go=99 with a moby/moby/
# client or fsouza/go-dockerclient user; R767 TS-
# Node=99 with an apocas/dockerode user; R768 124th
# language.
#
# WHY bollard IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-44 OPENER:
#
#   fussybeaver/bollard by Niel Drummond is the de-
#   facto Rust Docker Engine API client — a pure-
#   Rust async wrapper around the Docker daemon's
#   REST API + Unix socket / TCP / SSH transport
#   protocols.  Distinguishing characteristics:
#     1. PURE RUST — no CGo bindings to libdocker
#        (which doesn't really exist anyway);
#        compiles to statically-linked binaries with
#        no shared-library dependencies
#     2. ASYNC-FIRST — every Docker API operation
#        is async (returns Future) via tokio or
#        async-std runtimes; suitable for high-
#        concurrency tooling that manages many
#        containers in parallel
#     3. STREAMING API SUPPORT — `containers.logs()`
#        returns a Stream of LogOutput messages;
#        `containers.stats()` streams real-time
#        CPU/memory/network stats; `containers.exec()`
#        returns bidirectional streams for stdin/
#        stdout/stderr.  No polling loops
#     4. AUTO-GENERATED API TYPES — bollard's types
#        are generated from Docker's OpenAPI
#        specification, ensuring every field
#        documented by Docker is type-safe-
#        accessible from Rust
#     5. SSL + UNIX SOCKET + TCP + HTTPS_HYPER —
#        feature flags select transport: `ssl` for
#        SSL/TLS HTTPS, default for Unix socket;
#        also supports SSH-tunneled Docker daemons
#        via the `webpki` feature
#     6. ~2,200+ STARS ON fussybeaver/bollard
#     7. ECOSYSTEM-DOMINANT — used by dockrtui
#        (this completion), DataDog/lading (load
#        testing), enclaver-io/enclaver, faradayio/
#        cage, illacloud/illa, mxseev/logram, and
#        many other Rust Docker tools
#
# Maintained under github.com/fussybeaver/bollard.
# License: Apache-2.0.
#
# Cross-language CLI library taxonomy after R765:
#   * 123 languages
#   * 475 total CLI library variants (Rust 99 / Go 98 /
#     TS-Node 98)
#   * Axis 9 / Logging: 6/6/6 three-language symmetric
#   * Axes 10 + 13 + 14: 2/2/2 three-language symmetric
#   * 36 axes at 1/1/1 three-language symmetric
#   * Axis 44 opens with Rust=bollard (this round);
#     pending Go + TS-Node companions
#
# Comparison to other Axis 44 candidates (Rust):
#   * bollard (R765 THIS) — fussybeaver's async
#     Rust Docker client; ~2,200 stars
#   * docker-api-rs — older Rust Docker client;
#     less actively maintained
#   * dockworker — minimal Docker socket wrapper;
#     synchronous; smaller scope
#   * shiplift — abandoned; predecessor to bollard
#
# bollard is the chosen Axis 44 opener because:
#   - It is the modern de-facto Rust Docker API
#     client that EVERY new Rust Docker-CLI uses
#   - dockrtui uses bollard v0.19 with `ssl`
#     feature as a DIRECT dependency in Cargo.toml
#   - It is the closest functional analog to Go's
#     moby/moby/client (the official Docker Go
#     client) or fsouza/go-dockerclient, and TS-
#     Node's apocas/dockerode (the dominant Node
#     Docker client)
#   - Demonstrates the async-Rust + auto-generated-
#     from-OpenAPI pattern that distinguishes modern
#     Rust API clients from earlier shell-out-based
#     wrappers
#
# Pending companion picks for Axis 44:
#   - Go=99: a Go CLI tool prominently using
#            moby/moby/client (Docker's official
#            Go client) OR fsouza/go-dockerclient
#            (the older third-party Go Docker
#            client) as headline Docker library
#   - TS-Node=99: a Node.js CLI tool prominently
#            using apocas/dockerode (the dominant
#            Node Docker client; ~4,500 stars) as
#            headline Docker library
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# THE dockrtui CLI
#
# dockrtui is a TUI application with NO command-line
# flags beyond the standard --help / --version that
# clap-style binaries provide.  Invocation:
#   dockrtui
#
# All interaction once launched is keyboard-driven
# within the ratatui dashboard.  Connection to the
# Docker daemon is automatic via the socket-
# detection logic described below.
#
# Environment variables:
#   DOCKER_HOST                       Docker socket
#                                     URI (same as
#                                     Docker CLI;
#                                     e.g. unix:///
#                                     var/run/
#                                     docker.sock,
#                                     tcp://...,
#                                     ssh://...)
#
# Socket detection priority:
#   1. $DOCKER_HOST                   if set
#   2. Rootless Docker                /run/user/$UID/
#                                     docker.sock
#   3. Rootful Docker                 /var/run/
#                                     docker.sock
#
# Terminal requirements:
#   Minimum size                      70 columns × 28
#                                     rows
#   Backend                           crossterm
#                                     (cross-platform
#                                     terminal API)
#   Recommended TERM                  xterm-256color
#                                     or any terminal
#                                     supporting
#                                     truecolor +
#                                     unicode
#
# Common invocations:
#   # Launch dockrtui against the default Docker socket
#   dockrtui
#
#   # Launch against a specific Docker host via env
#   DOCKER_HOST=tcp://docker-host.local:2375 dockrtui
#   DOCKER_HOST=ssh://user@remote.host dockrtui
#   DOCKER_HOST=unix:///custom/docker.sock dockrtui
#
#   # Launch in a tmux split for side-by-side with editor
#   tmux split-window -h dockrtui
#
#   # Launch on a remote host via SSH
#   ssh remote-host -t 'dockrtui'
#
# Installation:
#   cargo install dockrtui              # from crates.io
#   # Or pre-built binaries from
#   # https://github.com/LuuNa-JD/dockrtui/releases
#
# In-TUI keyboard bindings (verify against repo
# README for current bindings — they are NOT exposed
# via clap flags so this completion file doesn't
# enumerate them, but typical: arrow keys / hjkl for
# navigation, / for search, s/S start/stop, r restart,
# d delete, e exec shell, q quit, ? help).
#
# OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/LuuNa-JD/dockrtui/blob/main/src/main.rs):
#
#   (no command-line flags; pure TUI with implicit
#    --help / --version standard handling)
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

_arguments -C \
    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
    && ret=0

return ret
